# HEYDAY server

- ESM (`import`/`export`); default export `db` from `server/db.js`
- DB path: `process.env.DATABASE_PATH` or default `heyday.db` at repo root (Railway: `/data/heyday.db` on mounted volume)
- New tables/columns: add to `runMigrations()` in `server/lib/migrate.js` idempotently
- Routes: `server/routes/*.js`, mounted in `server/index.js` under `/api/*`
- Protected routes use `authMiddleware`; `req.user` available after auth
- Use `db.transaction()` for multi-step deletes; respect FK order with `foreign_keys ON`
- Activity: `logActivity()` from `server/lib/activity.js`

When adding endpoints, match existing JSON shapes and error `{ error: string }` pattern.

## Checklist templates

- `template_tasks` columns: title, timing_*, sort_order, `default_role`, `calendar_nickname`
- `server/lib/deriveNickname.js` — short nicknames from titles; backfill via `_migrations` in migrate.js
- `checklists.js` — CRUD includes nickname + default_role on task POST/PUT
- `tasks.js` TASK_SELECT joins `tt.calendar_nickname` for calendar display

## Marketing

- `marketing_birthday_pins` — `(month, contact_id)` PK; `GET/PUT /api/marketing/birthday-pins`
- `PATCH /api/crm/:id` — `birthday`, `anniversary` in PATCH_FIELDS for contact edits from UI
